Reasoning: The paper focuses on the issue of high drop-out rates in Computer Science courses, particularly at the undergraduate level, and proposes the use of visual and textual programming languages to increase interest and retention of young learners. This suggests a focus on education (cs.ED) and cybernetics (cs.CY), as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of the use of programming languages. Additionally, the paper may touch on software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of improving the effectiveness of programming education.
